How to define MPTS processing:


- whether to regenerate PAT, or just change TSID field of PAT
- whether to snoop PMT, and add it to regenerated PAT
- whether to drop and regenerate PMT, or passthru untouched
- whether to remap ES, and regenerate PMT
- whether to drop or passthru ghost pids
- whether we can ask user to specify a list of PIDs to passthru
- how to support dropped pids


---------------------

PAT handling:
  - regenerate, or restamp TSID

PMT handling:
  - snoop (must, to show CLI)
  - change program number?
  - remap PMT pid?
  - regenerate (only if we remap ES pids)

ES handling (ES are TP whose pid is in PMT):
  - remap?
  - ES filtering supported?

Ghost pid handling:
  - drop, or passthru
  - need to check CC error?

----------------------

Session flags, and their impact:

es_remap: whether to remap ES pids
  - remap ES pids
  - regenerate PMT tables

pmt_remap: whether to remap PMT pids
  - regenerate PAT table

-----------------------

Always regenerate PAT:
  - avoid PAT tweaking (simplify code)
  - precious PAT placement possible
  - support passthru, or muxing

Always snoop PAT?

-----------------------

PID filtering:
- default is to include all PMT pids in PAT, and all ES pids in PMTs
- provide a list of blocked pids, user need to specify the blocked pid list
- to drop a program, add the PMT pid to the blocked pid list
- to drop an ES, add the ES pid to the blocked pid list
- blocked pid list will be added to pid table, with drop flag set

PID insertion:
- default is all pids not referenced in PAT/PMT will be dropped
- dropped PIDs will not be CC checked
- Provide a list of passthru pids, user need to specify the list
- Passthru pids will be forwarded to all outputs without pid remapping


